1. Using Triple-Quotes
it is used to split a large string into a multiline Python string. 

\\code\\
multiline_string = '''This is a \n
multiline
string.'''
print(multiline_string)

\\o\p\\
This is a
multiline
string.




2. Using parentheses and single/double quotes.

\\code\\
colors = ("multi-line string\n"
		"red \n"
		"blue \n"
		"green \n"
		"yellow "
		)

print(colors)

\\o\p\\
multi-line string
red 
blue 
green 
yellow 




3.Using Backslash
It is used to combine text that consists of individual lines.

\\code\\
x = "multiline String " \
	"I love Python" \
	"Python Langauge"
print(x)

\\o\p\\
multiline String I love PythonPython Langauge




4.Using join().

\\code\\
x = ' '.join(("multiline String ",
			"Python Language",
			"Welcome to GFG"))
print(x)

\\o\p\\
multiline String  Python Language Welcome to GFG




5.Using string.format().
 it is used to format strings

\\code\\
car = "Ferrari"
price = 250000

x = "Hello, The price of {} is {}".format(car, price)

print(x)

\\o\p\\
Hello, The price of Ferrari is 250000





6.Using % in Python.
 it is used to format strings

\\code\\
name = "Rahul"
points = 1000

x = "Hello, %s! You have %d coins." % (name, points)

print(x)

\\o\p\\
Hello, Rahul! You have 1000 coins.

 


